logic:
use map to hold the sum with its count
if map contains sum while itearte then add the count into the count
  why we are checking sum in map becoz same sum exist means the subarray count =0
we are holding the count so that we can add the number of times
        sumMap.put(0,1); -> to initilize

class Solution {
    public int findSubarray(int[] arr) {
        // code here.
        int count =0;
        int sum =0;
        
        Map<Integer,Integer> sumMap= new HashMap<Integer,Integer>();
        sumMap.put(0,1);
        for (int num: arr){
            sum = sum+num;
            
            if(sumMap.containsKey(sum)){
                count= count+ sumMap.get(sum);
            }
            sumMap.put(sum,sumMap.getOrDefault(sum,0)+1);
        }
        return count;
    }
}
